properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 20 at 1:33AM EST until February 22 at 3:00AM EST by NWS Jacksonville FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds increasing to 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 40
kt tonight. North winds 30 to 35 knots with gusts up to 40 knots
on Friday. Seas building to 7 to 12 feet tonight and 10 to 16
feet on Friday.

* WHERE...All Northeast Florida coastal waters from Fernandina
Beach FL to Flagler Beach FL out to 60 NM.

* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to 3 AM EST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 3 AM EST SATURDAY
